DESCRIPTION:Event Types: Arts\,Music\,Special Events\,Tourism\,Youth<br>
 Neighborhoods: Citywide\,Uptown<br>Sponsoring Organization: Seattle Offi
 ce of Arts & Culture\, Seattle Center\, Uptown Arts & Culture Coalition
 \, Climate Pledge Arena\, Seattle Kraken<br>Contact: Zach Frimmel<br>Cont
 act Phone: (206) 963-9226<br>Contact Email: Zach.Frimmel@seattle.gov<br>
 Audience: Adults\,All\,Children\,Family\,Pets\,Senior\,Special Needs\,Te
 en<br>Pre-Register: No<br>Cost: Free<br>Link: https://www.seattlecenter.
 com/events/event-calendar/artists-at-the-center-malika-lee<br><br>This e
 vent features a fun\, engaging experience where the author &amp\; audien
 ce members read children&#8217\;s book\, <em>How To Be Big Like Ants</em
 > together. The reading will be backed by live\, groovy music creating a
  memorable storytelling experience where the artists &amp\; audience wor
 k together to create a memorable storytelling experience. Includes up to
  50 book giveaway to kids.<br><br><strong>Featured Artists:</strong><ul>
  <li>Malika Lee - author/storyteller/vocals	</li><li>Kelvin Penn - keybo
 ard/vocals	</li><li>Khan Overcast - bass/vocals&#160\;</li></ul><hr><a h
 ref="https://www.seattlecenter.com/events/featured-events/artists-at-the
 -center" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Artists At the Center</a> is a m
 ulti-year collaboration between Seattle Office of Arts &amp\; Culture an
 d Seattle Center\, with support from Uptown Arts &amp\; Culture Coalitio
 n and the communities adjacent to Seattle Center campus. The project is 
 made possible by a 10-year grant from Climate Pledge Arena and Seattle K
 raken.
