DESCRIPTION:Event Types: Arts\,Dance\,Ethnic/Cultural\,Special Events\,T
 ourism<br>Neighborhoods: Citywide\,Uptown<br>Sponsoring Organization: Se
 attle Office of Arts & Culture\, Seattle Center\, Uptown Arts & Culture 
 Coalition\, Climate Pledge Arena\, Seattle Kraken<br>Contact: Zach Frimm
 el<br>Contact Phone: (206) 963-9226<br>Contact Email: Zach.Frimmel@seatt
 le.gov<br>Audience: Adults\,All\,Children\,Family\,Pets\,Senior\,Special
  Needs\,Teen<br>Pre-Register: No<br>Cost: Free<br>Link: https://www.seat
 tlecenter.com/events/event-calendar/artists-at-the-center-anu-samrat<br>
 <br>A kaleidoscope of movement &amp\; mood portrayed in all 8 styles of 
 Indian classical dance! (Bharatanatyam\, Mohiniyattam\, Kathakali\, Kuch
 ipudi from south India\, Odissi\, Manipuri and Sattriya from east India 
 and Kathak from the north).<br><br>Concept\, music\, and choreography by
  Anu Samrat.<hr><a href="https://www.seattlecenter.com/events/featured-e
 vents/artists-at-the-center" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Artists At t
 he Center</a> is a multi-year collaboration between Seattle Office of Ar
 ts &amp\; Culture and Seattle Center\, with support from Uptown Arts &am
 p\; Culture Coalition and the communities adjacent to Seattle Center cam
 pus. The project is made possible by a 10-year grant from Climate Pledge
  Arena and Seattle Kraken.
