DESCRIPTION:Event Types: Community\,Ethnic/Cultural\,Music\,Training-Cla
 sses/Workshops<br>Neighborhoods: Central Area/Squire Park<br>Sponsoring 
 Organization: LANGSTON<br>Contact: Jahi McGhee<br>Contact Phone: 2066844
 758<br>Contact Email: langston.institute@seattle.gov<br>Audience: All<br
 >Pre-Register: Yes<br>Cost: Free<br>Link: https://www.langstonseattle.or
 g/programs/healing-drum-workshop/<br><br><strong>Drums are provided. All
  ages. No experience necessary.</strong><br><br>The Hawk Foundation for 
 Research and Education in African Culture&#160\;brings master drummers t
 o LANGSTON to engage in a well-researched pedagogy of community healing 
 through African drumming.<br><br>The Hawk Foundation is a Washington-bas
 ed drum and education organization that utilizes West African and Africa
 n American music to promote education\, team bonding\, organizational de
 velopment\, and research-based therapy. Through history\, Yoruba stories
  and classic drum rhythms\, this class has reconnected students to the d
 rum\, the past\, and themselves.
