SUMMARY:Kim Samek discusses I Am the Ghost Here w/ Josh Riedel
LOCATION:Elliott Bay Book Company
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260331T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260331T200000
X-MICROSOFT-CDO-ALLDAYEVENT:FALSE
URL:https://www.elliottbaybook.com/events/49708
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Event Type";ID=21;TYPE=number:Master Submissi
 on Form Template
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Neighborhoods";ID=11388;TYPE=CustomAsset:Capi
 tol Hill
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Event Types";ID=11444;TYPE=CustomAsset:Arts
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Audience";ID=10952;TYPE=CustomAsset:Adults
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Contact";ID=10948;TYPE=SingleLine:Kim samek
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Contact Phone";ID=10950;TYPE=PhoneUS:31097590
 39
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Contact Email";ID=10949;TYPE=Email:<a href="m
 ailto:ksamek@gmail.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">ksamek@gmail.com<
 /a>
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Pre-Register";ID=10961;TYPE=Boolean:No
X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Cost";ID=10963;TYPE=SingleLine:Free
DTSTAMP:20260323T082812Z
DESCRIPTION:Neighborhoods: Capitol Hill<br>Event Types: Arts<br>Audience
 : Adults<br>Contact: Kim samek<br>Contact Phone: 3109759039<br>Contact E
 mail: ksamek@gmail.com<br>Pre-Register: No<br>Cost: Free<br>Link: https:
 //www.elliottbaybook.com/events/49708<br><br>Kim Samek w/ Josh Riedel<br
 >Tuesday March 31st\, 2026 @ 7:00PM - 8:00 PM<br><br>Writer and televisi
 on producer Kim Samek discusses her debut collection I Am the Ghost Here
 : Stories\, in which twelve women confront the mounting existential terr
 ors of modern life. Warm\, endlessly strange\, and filled with dark yet 
 hopeful humor\, I Am the Ghost Here casts familiar crises of contemporar
 y life in a wholly unique light\, offering a pathway towards our shared 
 humanity even as reality comes crumbling down. She is joined by Portland
  writer Josh Riedel. <br><br>Registration is not required\, but helps us
  anticipate audience size. If you&#39\;d like to RSVP\, please do so her
 e!<br><br>A woman&#39\;s limbs disappear into &#8220\;the cloud&#8221\; 
 during wildfire-induced power outages. A lonely DoorDasher accidentally 
 becomes the star of someone else&#39\;s reality show\, forced to resolve
  her fraught relationship with her immigrant mother for the narrative. S
 uccumbing to a widely denied pandemic\, a gymnastics coach must carry he
 r heart around in a Mason jar\, using her disability to become an influe
 ncer. Two chronically single\, chronically ill people become soulmates\,
  only to discover their meeting was algorithmically orchestrated by ad t
 ech. Other dramas unfold as icebergs melt and island-sized trash heaps b
 urn.<br><br>Threaded with sharp social commentary\, these stories questi
 on the engineering of human connection through technology\, social media
 \, and reality television. Warm\, endlessly strange\, and filled with da
 rk yet hopeful humor\, I Am the Ghost Here casts familiar crises of cont
 emporary life in a wholly unique light\, offering a pathway towards our 
 shared humanity even as reality comes crumbling down.<br><br>Kim Samek i
 s a half-Thai Emmy-nominated writer and television producer with credits
  including MTV&#39\;s Catfish and PBS&#39\; WordGirl. She studied German
  Literature and creative writing at Stanford University. Her stories app
 ear in Guernica\, Ecotone\, Electric Literature\, The North American Rev
 iew\, The Chicago Quarterly Review\, swamp pink\, Gulf Coast\, The South
 ern Humanities Review\, The Threepenny Review\, Story\, and ZYZZYVA. Her
  short fiction has won a Pushcart Prize. A native of Seattle\, she lives
  in Los Angeles.<br><br>Josh Riedel is the author of the novel Please Re
 port Your Bug Here\, called a &#8220\;sharp literary thriller&#8221\; by
  The New York Times and selected as an Amazon Editors&#8217\; Pick in &#
 8220\;Best Science Fiction &amp\; Fantasy.&#8221\; The recipient of fell
 owships from MacDowell and Yaddo\, his writing appears in Esquire\, Elec
 tric Literature\, Joyland\, and One Story\, among others. He lives in Po
 rtland\, Oregon.
CATEGORIES:City-Wide
UID:http://uid.trumba.com/event/199297043
X-TRUMBA-LINK:https://www.seattle.gov/event-calendar?trumbaEmbed=view%3d
 event%26eventid%3d199297043
END:VEVENT
