DESCRIPTION:Neighborhoods: Laurelhurst/Sand Point\,University District\,
 Wedgwood/View Ridge<br>Contact: Ann Forrest\, OEM Volunteer<br>Contact E
 mail: OEM_StopTheBleed@Seattle.gov<br>Audience: Adults\,Senior\,Special 
 Needs\,Teen<br>Pre-Register: Yes<br>Cost: Free<br>Link: https://www.seat
 tle.gov/emergency-management/community-engagement/stop-the-bleed<br><br>
 Life-threatening bleeding injuries can happen anytime. When they do\, ev
 ery minute counts! Stop the Bleed empowers participants to take action! 
 Our trained instructors teach the community about bleeding control: reco
 gnizing life-threatening bleeding\, applying pressure to the wound\, and
  using a tourniquet.
