DTSTAMP:20260309T090253Z
DESCRIPTION:Event Types: Arts\,Community\,Museum/Gallery\,Special Events
 <br>Civic Poet: Dujie Tahat<br>Neighborhoods: Citywide\,Pioneer Square<b
 r>Contact: Rana San<br>Contact Phone: (206) 256-6279<br>Contact Email: R
 ana.San@seattle.gov<br>Audience: All<br>Pre-Register: No<br>Cost: Free<b
 r><br><p><strong>Join ARTS at King Street Station for First Thursday Art
  Walk in Pioneer Square&#160\;to celebrate National Poetry Month with Ci
 vic Poet Dujie Tahat and</strong>&#160\;<strong>DJ Sureal on the decks</
 strong><strong>!</strong><br><br>Visit the gallery\, listen to music\, a
 nd read poetry from a selection curated by Dujie. The evening will be pu
 nctuated by occasional voiced readings.<br><br><em>Photo: Mark Harazim</
 em></p><hr><p>Gallery hours are Wed. &#8211\; Sat. 11 a.m. &#8211\; 5 p.
 m.\; First Thursdays 11 a.m. &#8211\; 8:00 p.m.<br><br><strong>About Duj
 ie Tahat</strong>:<br><strong><a href="https://dujietahat.com/" target="
 _blank" rel="noopener">Dujie Tahat</a></strong>&#160\;is a poet and crit
 ic living and working in Washington state. They are the author of three 
 poetry chapbooks:&#160\;Here I Am O My God\,&#160\;selected for a Poetry
  Society of America Chapbook Fellowship\;&#160\;Salat\,&#160\;winner of 
 the Tupelo Press Sunken Garden Chapbook Award and longlisted for the 202
 0 PEN/Voelcker Award for Poetry Collection\; and&#160\;Balikbayan\,&#160
 \;finalist for The New Michigan Press / DIAGRAM chapbook contest and the
  Center for Book Arts honoree.<br><br>Dujie has earned fellowships from 
 the National Book Critics Circle\, Hugo House\, Jack Straw Writing Progr
 am\, and the Poetry Incubator\, as well as scholarships from Bread Loaf 
 and Sewanee Writers&#8217\; Conference. Along with Luther Hughes and Gab
 rielle Bates\, they cohost The Poet Salon podcast. Dujie serves as Criti
 c-at-Large for Poetry Northwest and poetry editor for&#160\;Moss.&#160\;
 They got their start as a Seattle Poetry Slam Finalist\, a collegiate gr
 and slam champion\, and Seattle Youth Speaks Grand Slam Champion\, repre
 senting Seattle at HBO&#8217\;s&#160\;Brave New Voices.</p>
CATEGORIES:Arts and Culture
