DESCRIPTION:Building Name / Room Number / Site: Ceremonial Room<br>Event
  Description: There&rsquo\;s something quietly powerful about gathering 
 in a place where history still breathes. At the Duwamish Longhouse\, sto
 ries are not just remembered&mdash\;they&rsquo\;re felt. And the annual 
 Princess Angeline Spring Tea invites you into one of those stories. Prin
 cess Angeline Kikisoblu\, the daughter of Chief Seattle\, lived her life
  in the very land where this gathering takes place. She witnessed immens
 e change &mdash\; displacement\, loss\, and transformation&mdash\; yet r
 emained deeply connected to her homeland and her people. Her presence\, 
 resilience\, and strength continue to echo through generations. Attendin
 g this tea isn&rsquo\;t just about enjoying a beautiful afternoon&mdash
 \;it&rsquo\;s about stepping into that legacy. As you sit with a warm cup
  of tea\, thoughtfully prepared by The Red Tea Room\, you&rsquo\;re shar
 ing in a tradition of community and reflection. The setting is intention
 al: the Longhouse itself symbolizes cultural continuity and respect\, ma
 king it the perfect place to pause and honor the past. We are especially
  honored to welcome Heather Pihl as this year&rsquo\;s guest speaker. He
 r reflections will help bring deeper understanding to Princess Angeline&
 rsquo\;s enduring legacy and the importance of remembering her story tod
 ay. People attend this annual tea because it offers something rare: a ch
 ance to slow down\, to listen\, and to connect&mdash\; with history\, wi
 th community\, and with the enduring story of the Duwamish Tribe. It&rsq
 uo\;s not just an event. It&rsquo\;s a moment of remembrance rooted in p
 lace\, culture\, and shared understanding.<br>Neighborhoods: Alki/Admira
 l\,Delridge/North Delridge\,Downtown Commercial Core\,Duwamish/SODO\,Fau
 ntleroy/Morgan Junction/Seaview\,Georgetown\,Magnolia\,Mt. Baker/North R
 ainier\,North Beach/Blue Ridge\,North Capitol Hill\,North of Seattle\,Pi
 oneer Square\,Queen Anne\,Ravenna/Bryant/Roosevelt\,Seward Park\,Univers
 ity District\,Uptown\,Wallingford\,Wedgwood/View Ridge\,West of Seattle
 \,West Seattle Junction/Genesee Hill<br>Event Types: Community\,Ethnic/Cu
 ltural\,Museum/Gallery\,Special Events\,Tourism<br>Audience: Adults\,Fam
 ily\,Senior<br>Sponsoring Organization: Duwamish Longhouse & Cultural Ce
 nter<br>Contact: events@duwamishtribe.org<br>Contact Phone: 206-431-1582
 <br>Contact Email: events@duwamishtribe.org<br>Site Contact Details: Fre
 e Parking\, Parking at the longhouse and in lot north of longhouse.<br>P
