 png">www.trumba.com&#8230\;</a>
DTSTAMP:20260304T131231Z
DESCRIPTION:Event Types: Arts\,Community\,Museum/Gallery\,Music\,Special
  Events<br>Neighborhoods: Citywide\,Pioneer Square<br>Contact: Rana San<
 br>Contact Phone: (206) 256-6279<br>Contact Email: Rana.San@seattle.gov<
 br>Audience: All<br>Pre-Register: No<br>Cost: Free<br><br><p><strong>Joi
 n ARTS at King Street Station for <em>The Dreaming Room: Soundscapes for
  Deep Rest</em>\,</strong> <strong>a concert series&#160\;hosted by Step
 hanie Ann Ball.</strong><br><br>This community-rooted concert series is 
 designed to support nervous system recovery\, emotional release\, and co
 llective connections through sound meditation\, music\, and storytelling
 . Come rest and connect over the course of this renewing series\, every 
 other month on the third Thursday&#160\;between February and December.<b
 r><br><em>We Still Dream a Future</em>&#160\;is&#160\;a series of free p
 ublic art activations\, installations\, exhibitions\, performances\, and
  learning experiences designed to help us dream\, learn\, and grow\, tak
 ing place&#160\;throughout the Downtown core.<br><br><strong>SERIES SCHE
 DULE (3rd Thursdays)</strong>:</p><ul> <li>February 19&#160\;&#8212\;&#1
 60\;rejuvenation + renewal	</li><li>April 16&#160\;&#8212\;&#160\;creati
 vity\, fun\, expansion	</li><li>June 18&#160\;&#8212\;&#160\;joyful\, wo
 ndrous playtime	</li><li>August 20&#160\;&#8212\;&#160\;transitioning	</
 li><li>October 15&#160\;&#8212\;&#160\;gratitude + reflection	</li><li>D
 ecember 17&#160\;&#8212\;&#160\;celebration + releasing</li></ul><hr><p>
 Gallery hours are Wed. &#8211\; Sat. 11 a.m. &#8211\; 5 p.m.\; First Thu
 rsdays 11 a.m. &#8211\; 8:00 p.m.<br><br><strong>Artist bio:<br><a href=
 "https://stephanieannball.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Stephanie
  Ann Ball</a></strong> is&#160\;a healing artist and sound meditation fa
 cilitator. Her work sits at the intersection of therapeutic sound\, scie
 nce\, and well-being. Using sound meditation\, energy work\, and subcons
 cious reprogramming techniques\, Stephanie helps individuals and teams r
 egulate the nervous system\, release stress\, and access states of calm
 \, clarity\, and flow. The best part? It all starts with something easy a
 nd fun&#8212\;listening to music.</p>
CATEGORIES:Arts and Culture
UID:http://uid.trumba.com/event/194911609
X-TRUMBA-LINK:https://www.seattle.gov/event-calendar?trumbaEmbed=view%3d
 event%26eventid%3d194911609
END:VEVENT
