 l="noopener" title="https://www.trumba.com/i/DgAYz08nsGYob38u%2AOkXGvL2.
 jpg">www.trumba.com&#8230\;</a>
DTSTAMP:20260310T094531Z
DESCRIPTION:Event Types: Arts\,Community\,Museum/Gallery\,Music\,Special
  Events<br>Neighborhoods: Citywide\,Pioneer Square<br>Contact: Rana San<
 br>Contact Phone: (206) 256-6279<br>Contact Email: Rana.San@seattle.gov<
 br>Audience: All<br>Pre-Register: No<br>Cost: Free<br><br><p><strong>Joi
 n ARTS at King Street Station for <em>Sound Medicine for Liberation and 
 Healing</em>\,&#160\;a series of sound medicine offerings&#160\;hosted b
 y Tory Trujillo.</strong><br><br>Now\, more than ever\, we need opportun
 ities to rest\, release grief and rage\, gather in safe space\, feel sup
 ported\, and give our nervous systems a chance to shift into the &#8220
 \;safe and connected mode.&quot\; Through this series of sound medicine o
 fferings\, artist Tory Trujillo supports our collective healing\, ground
 ing\, and restoration.<br><br>Join us for six sessions throughout 2026\,
  on the second Thursdays of March\, April\, May\, October\, November\, a
 nd December.<br><br><em>We Still Dream a Future</em>&#160\;is&#160\;a se
 ries of free public art activations\, installations\, exhibitions\, perf
 ormances\, and learning experiences designed to help us dream\, learn\, 
 and grow\, taking place&#160\;throughout the Downtown core.<br><br><stro
 ng>SERIES SCHEDULE (2nd Thursdays)</strong>:</p><ul> <li>March 12	</li><
 li>April 9	</li><li>May 14	</li><li>October 8	</li><li>November 12	</li>
 <li>December 10</li></ul><hr><p>Gallery hours are Wed. &#8211\; Sat. 11 
 a.m. &#8211\; 5 p.m.\; First Thursdays 11 a.m. &#8211\; 8:00 p.m.<br><br
 ><strong>Artist bio:</strong><br><a href="https://www.torytrujillo.com/"
  target="_blank" rel="noopener"><strong>Tory Trujillo</strong></a> is a 
 Two-Spirit\, Mixed-Blood Mexican Indigenous Facilitator of Healing and P
 rofessional Vocalist. Her Modalities include Sound Medicine\, Ritual\, B
 odywork\, and Energy work. Her transformational sound medicine sessions 
 are informed by her ancestral lineage and enhanced through additional tr
 aining.</p>
CATEGORIES:Arts and Culture
