 et their imaginations run wild to fulfill secret longings. Fluent in the
  language of circus\, Acrobatic Conundrum’s principal performers melt th
 e fourth wall to reveal their flaws and journeys to redemption. The audi
 ence plays a vital part in The Circus of Second Chances\, in which ropes
  are dancescapes\, trapezes are windows to the soul\, and spinning hoops
  are portals to infinite possibility. In our homes we are out at sea\, o
 n our living room couch we find ourselves on an epic odyssey\; so much r
 ests upon the fate of a dozen lemons. Leveraging their long running frie
 ndships with each other\, Emma Curtiss\, Melissa Knowles\, and Terry Cra
 ne put all their talents and quirky craftiness into this dada circus rom
 p. They climb\, cavort\, invert\, revert\, and subvert in this capriciou
 s acrobatic piece as they ask\, “What does your heart wish for?”Appropri
 ate for all ages. 90 minutes\, no intermission.Featuring rope acrobatics
 \, Cyr wheel\, handbalancing\, slack rope\, live baking\, and clown. Per
 formers: Emma Curtiss\, Melissa Knowles\, and Terry Crane. Music written
  and performed by Kamila Nasr.Director: Terry CraneSound and Scenic Desi
