X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Event Description";ID=18998;TYPE=MultiLine:Th
 e Pioneer Square Preservation Board reviews applications for Certificate
 s of Approval for changes of use and exterior architectural alterations 
 in the district and recommends approval\, approval with conditions\, or 
 denial to the Director of the Department of Neighborhoods\, who makes fi
 nal decisions concerning applications. The Board may also make recommend
 ations to the Mayor\, the City Council\, and any public or private agenc
 ies concerning land use and social issues in the District. The Board bas
 es its decisions on the standards established in the District Ordinance 
 (SMC 23.66)\, Rules for the Pioneer Square Preservation District and the
  Secretary of the Interior&#39\;s Standards for Rehabilitation.
