 :<p><strong>Public Comment Guide</strong></p><p>We accept public comment
 s on matters pertaining to our agenda.</p><ul> <li>Speakers should regis
 ter either 1). by emailing the commission or 2). by signing up in-person
  at the meeting itself in order to be recognized by the Chair.</li></ul>
 <p>&#160\; 1). To register\, send an email to <a href="mailto:centercomm
 ission@seattle.gov" target="_blank" rel="noopener">centercommission@seat
 tle.gov</a> with &#8220\;public comment&#8221\; in the subject line by 1
 0:00 AM on the day of the meeting.<strong> </strong></p><p>2). Alternati
 vely\, sign up to speak on the public comment sign-up sheet located insi
 de the meeting room at least 15 minutes prior to each Seattle Center Adv
 isory Commission meeting.</p><ul> <li>Each speaker may be allotted up to
  two minutes to speak.	</li><li>In addition to topics on the agenda\, th
 e Chair may allow public comment on other topics.	</li><li>If you are un
 able to attend the meeting in-person or remotely\, please submit written
  comments to <u><a href="mailto:centercommission@seattle.gov" target="_b
 lank" rel="noopener">centercommission@seattle.gov</a></u></li></ul>
