 nal District\,Columbia City\,Delridge/North Delridge\,Downtown Commercia
 l Core\,Duwamish/SODO\,First Hill\,High Point\,Judkins Park\,Madison Par
 k\,Madrona/Leschi\,Miller Park\,Mt. Baker/North Rainier\,Pioneer Square
 \,Rainier Beach/Othello\,Roxhill/Westwood/White Center\,Seward Park\,Sout
 h Beacon Hill/New Holly\,West of Seattle\,West Seattle Junction/Genesee 
 Hill<br>Location Type: Outdoor<br>Parks: Amy Yee Tennis Center<br>Sponso
 ring Organization: Amy Yee Tennis Foundation<br>Contact: Carl Bergquist<
 br>Contact Email: aytfprogramming@gmail.com<br>Site Contact Details: Out
 doors. Subject to rain cancelation. We notify participants and volunteer
 s if rained out. Note just b/c rain may be happening in the city does no
 t mean the event is canceled. There is parking near the courts.<br>Audie
 nce: Adults\,Senior\,Teen<br>Pre-Register: Yes<br>Cost: Free<br>Link: ht
 tps://amyyee10usfoundation.org/<br><br>This is a free 4-week series for 
 youth to &#39\;try&#39\; or be introduced to tennis in a fun played base
 d approach. Rackets\, etc are all provided for participants and they usu
 ally receive a t-shirt. Volunteers do not have to be tennis players\, bu
 t it&#39\;s a bonus. Volunteers do everything from gathering balls\, &#3
 9\;partnering up&#39\; with kids in drills and simply playing in. Volunt
 eers also help set up/break down equipment\, etc. The event is hosted if
  dry. We offer pre-program training for those interested in May\, but no
 t required to participate. Volunteers are needed until roughly 1130am\, 
 but can stay later for other clinics. Teen volunteers can stay and play 
 during the High School section.
